crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is identified as the MSI Afterburner kernel driver (RTCore64.sys). While a legitimate utility, it is classified as SUSPICIOUS because it provides unrestricted kernel-level primitives to user-mode applications, a design flaw tracked as CVE-2019-16098. The driver allows mapping physical memory ('\Device\PhysicalMemory') via ZwMapViewOfSection, reading/writing Model Specific Registers (MSRs) via __rdmsr/__wrmsr, and direct Port I/O access. These capabilities are frequently exploited by threat actors in 'Bring Your Own Vulnerable Driver' (BYOVD) attacks to disable Endpoint Detection and Response (EDR) agents, bypass kernel protections, and escalate privileges. Relevant IOCs include the device name '\Device\RTCore64' and symbolic link '\DosDevices\RTCore64'.
